The paper proposes an end-to-end trainable approach for OCR on printed documents using semantic segmentation and object detection. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of large-scale datasets and deep learning techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for text recognition, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
